@node intro "WebChat - Introduction"


                                 @{b}WebChat - Introduction@{ub}


 Ever thought of running a mailing list?

   Too much trouble?

     Worried about noise?

       Want to keep it open to the public but closed to troublemakers?


  Then WebChat could be your answer, instead of a email based list have a web-based list.
  Now unless you have access to a fancy cgi script & a friendly ISP you'll have to find a way to use HTML Forms.
  This is where WebChat comes in; it will decode the forms output and convert it to a readable HTML page.

   1) You get your email.
   2) Save any chat emails.
   3) Click on the WebUpdate icon & select a saved email.
   4) Repeat for any other emails.
   5) Get your newly created chat.html & upload it onto your site.

  And that's basically that. Well in theory anyway :)

@endnode

