@node help "WebChat - Help tutorial"


                                 @{b}WebChat - Help@{ub}


 This script works by decoding the output from a FORM. It looks for three fields
 in this version:

             * formid - WebChat identifies the form by this.

             * name - name of the message writer

             * message - the message itself

 These are produced by a FORM that looks like this:

	<FORM method="POST" ACTION="mailto:??????@??????.??.??">

	<INPUT type="HIDDEN" name="formid" value="nfc">

	<B>Nickname:</B>
	<SELECT name="name">
	<OPTION selected value="Someone">Someone
	<OPTION value="newn">Other
	</SELECT>

	<P>
	<B>Add/change my nickname as:</B>
	<INPUT name="new" type="text" maxlength="11" value="Newnickname">
	<P>

	<B>Your message:</B><BR>
	<TEXTAREA name="message" rows="10" cols=40></TEXTAREA>
	<BR><BR>
	<INPUT type="submit" value="Send">
	<INPUT type="reset" value="Reset">

	</FORM>

 This is a section of the default-end in the HTML drawer.
 Note: Ability to change nickname is not yet implemented.

 You need to edit this file to suit the requrements e.g.

	<FORM method="POST" ACTION="mailto:??????@??????.??.??">

 Needs to be changed to include the mail address that you want the data posting to.

	<OPTION selected value="Someone">Someone

 Should be changed to what you want to be called.
 To add new names just add a line like this replacing newname with the desired name:

	<OPTION value="newname">newname

 The default-top file also in the HTML drawer contains the header file for the
 chat.html. You can put in any help & introduction text in this file along with
 any logos you wish to include.

